Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1268
A BILL FOR AN ACT concerning state offices and administration.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2025 (RETROACTIVE)] (a)
2 The following amounts appropriated in P.L.213-2025 to the
3 Indiana economic development corporation for the Indiana office
4 of defense development must be used exclusively to support
5 priorities identified by the Indiana defense task force established
6 by IC 4-3-21.5:
7 (1) Seven hundred eighty-two thousand four hundred forty-six
8 dollars ($782,446) for state fiscal year 2025-26.
9 (2) Seven hundred eighty-two thousand four hundred forty-six
10 dollars ($782,446) for state fiscal year 2026-27.
11 The Indiana economic development corporation shall consult with,
12 and receive approval from, the Indiana defense task force prior to
13 obligating or expending the funds. The Indiana defense task force
14 shall make a report detailing the use of the funds and their
15 correspondence to Indiana defense task force priorities to the
16 budget committee and the legislative council in an electronic
17 format under IC 5-14-6.
18 (b) This SECTION expires June 30, 2027.
